        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:29PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 729 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of San Acacia, or 22 miles northwest of Socorro,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Acacia, La Joya, Lemitar and Chamizal.

This includes Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 155 and 171.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
